## Deposit Methods Indian Traders Actually Use

Funding a Polymarket account from India requires moving cryptocurrency to the Polygon network. The typical flow involves purchasing USDC or MATIC through an Indian crypto exchange like WazirX or CoinDCX, then transferring to a self-custody wallet like MetaMask, and finally bridging or sending funds to Polygon if necessary. Polymarket accepts USDC deposits directly on Polygon, making the final step straightforward once funds reach a compatible wallet. Indian traders often face higher friction at the initial fiat-to-crypto conversion step, as domestic exchanges have varying policies around transfers to external wallets. Some traders route through peer-to-peer markets to acquire crypto before moving it onchain. The key consideration is maintaining clear records of all transactions, both for personal tracking and potential tax documentation requirements under Indian capital gains rules for crypto assets.

